    {
        "id": "example-comment",
        "type": "comment",
        "z": "energy-overview-example-flow",
        "name": "Energy Overview Widget Example",
        "info": "This flow demonstrates the Energy Overview widget.\n\n**How to use:**\n1. Click the \"Solar Production\" inject to simulate solar panels producing energy\n2. Click \"Grid Import\" to simulate importing from the grid\n3. Click \"Battery Charging\" to simulate battery charging from solar\n4. Click \"Stop All\" to disable all energy flows\n\n**Payload structure:**\n```json\n{\n  \"routes\": {\n    \"solarToInverter\": true,\n    \"inverterToHome\": true\n  },\n  \"labels\": {\n    \"solar\": { \"value\": \"3.2 kW\", \"sublabel\": \"Producing\" },\n    \"home\": { \"value\": \"1.5 kW\", \"sublabel\": \"Consuming\" }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Available routes:**\n- solarToInverter\n- inverterToHome\n- inverterToGrid / gridToInverter\n- inverterToBattery / batteryToInverter\n- inverterToCar / carToInverter",
        "x": 180,
        "y": 60,
        "wires": []
    },
    {
